elements.name: accountingClassCode1
elements.description:
CBP accounting classification code representing a specific fee type previously reported at the Entry Summary Header Fee (34-Record) or Line User Fee (62-Record) level.

  • Informal Merchandise Processing Fee.
  • Dutiable Mail Fee.
  • Manual Entry Surcharge.
  • Beef Fee.
  • Pork Fee.
  • Honey Fee.
  • Cotton Fee.
  • Raspberry Fee.
  • Sugar Fee.
  • Potato Fee.
  • Lime Fee.
  • Mushroom Fee.
  • Watermelon Fee.
  • Softwood Lumber Fee.
  • Blueberry Fee.
  • Avocado Fee.
  • Mango Fee.
  • Sorghum Fee.
  • Dairy Product Fee.
  • Formal Merchandise Processing Fee.
  • Harbor Maintenance Fee.

elements.name: totalFeeAmount1
elements.description: Total estimated fee amount that corresponds to Accounting Class Code (1) in U.S. dollars and cents. Two decimal places are implied.
